  <front>
   <head>SONNET TO SIMPLICITY.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">of the desert! on this lonely shore,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Simplicity, thy blessings still are mine,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And all thou canst not give I pleas'd resign,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">For all beside can soothe my soul no more.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I ask no lavish heaps to swell my store,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And purchase pleasures far remote from thine:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ye joys, for which the race of Europe pine,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Ah, not for me your studied grandeur pour;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Let me where yon tall cliffs are rudely pil'd,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where towers the Palm amidst the mountain trees,</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where pendant from the steep, with graces wild,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The blue Liana floats upon the breeze,</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Still haunt those bold recesses, Nature's child,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Where thy majestic charms my spirit seize!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
